From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 15:02:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] parseModule: honest RFHUB SEC16 status + proven key-count (no
 guessing)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The RFHUB branch reported 'SEC16 INVALID/MISMATCH' whenever the size-derived
0x050E mirror pair failed the legacy matched-pair+CS check — a false alarm
that implied an unsynced/wrong secret. Across the real dump corpus that's
wrong: most 6.2 hubs carry a matched per-car block at 0x050E, and the 592745
variant simply doesn't fit the recognized layout at either offset.

Purely additive (sec16valid/sec16match unchanged — all 24 RFH tests pass):
- info.sec16Status: verified-mirror | unverified-layout | blank. 'unverified-
  layout' replaces the misleading 'invalid' for bytes we can't validate from
  the file. Roles of 0x050E/0x0226 are NOT asserted (unproven).
- info.rfhKeyCountByte: 0x0150 (mirror 0x01D4), surfaced only when the two
  agree. PROVEN 0x02->0x03 across a same-VIN before/after key-add (615142).

Evidence + unknowns documented in RFHUB_GEN2_LAYOUT.md. Full suite: 5843
passed, same 7 pre-existing failures, zero new.
